  "response_text": "# Balance & Focus Routine\n\n## Daily Practice (15-20 minutes)\n\n**Warm-up (2 min)**\n- Gentle neck rolls and shoulder shrugs\n- Arm circles\n\n**Balance Work (8-10 min)**\n- Single-leg stands: 30 seconds each leg, 3 sets\n- Heel-to-toe walk: 20 steps forward, 20 back\n- Eyes-closed balance: 20-30 seconds per leg\n- Tree pose: 30-60 seconds each side\n\n**Focus Training (5-7 min)**\n- Meditation or breathwork (3-5 min)\n- Concentration exercise: follow a moving object with eyes only\n\n**Cool-down (1-2 min)**\n- Stretching major muscle groups\n\n## Additional Tips\n\n- **Consistency**: Practice 4-5 days/week for best results\n- **Progression**: Close your eyes during balance exercises to increase difficulty\n- **Environment**: Minimize distractions during focus work\n- **Sleep**: Aim for 7-9 hours—essential for both balance and cognition\n- **Nutrition**: Eat omega-3s and stay hydrated\n- **Variety**: Add yoga, tai chi, or dance for dynamic balance work\n\n## Quick Wins\n- Stand on one leg while brushing teeth\n- Take the stairs slowly, focusing on each step\n- Practice single-leg movements throughout the day\n\nStart slow and increase intensity gradually. Results typically appear within 2-3 weeks.",
